election_record.label: New Jersey 1820 U.S. House of Representatives

overview.note: Anti-Caucus tickets appeared in the Elizabeth-Town Gazette, The True American, and several other newspapers. All of these tickets were exclusively Republican with the exception of the one in The True American, which included two Federalists, Joseph C. Hornblower and John Frelinghuysen. Ephraim Bateman was included on both the Republican and Anti-Caucus tickets. No regular Federal ticket was organized, however a number of Federalists did receive scattered support.
"A New-Jersey paper mentions, that they have 119 candidates for their six seats in Congress." Delaware Gazette (Wilmington, DE). October 17, 1820.
